    <p class="lede">By using Queenzone (queenzone.org) you agree to these terms. Please read them.</p>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>Queenzone is an independent, fan-run archive of news, articles, photography, discography and community history. We are not affiliated with Queen or its representatives.</p>

    <h2>Your account</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for keeping your account credentials secure and for all activity that occurs under your account. You must be at least 13 years old to create an account. Accounts are personal and may not be transferred.</p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>When using Queenzone you must not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Post content that is unlawful, abusive, defamatory, or that infringes another person's rights.</li>
      <li>Spam, harass, or impersonate other users or staff.</li>
      <li>Attempt to disrupt, overload, or gain unauthorised access to Queenzone's systems.</li>
      <li>Use automated tools to scrape or harvest content without permission.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We reserve the right to remove content or suspend accounts that violate these rules.</p>

    <h2>Content you post</h2>
    <p>You retain ownership of content you post. By posting, you grant Queenzone a non-exclusive licence to display that content on the site. Please only post content you have the right to share.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>The Queenzone name, design, and original editorial content are our property. Archive material relating to Queen is used for fan and historical purposes. If you believe content infringes your rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@queenzone.org">privacy@queenzone.org</a>.</p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>Queenzone is provided "as is". We make no warranties about uptime, accuracy or completeness of content. We are not liable for any loss or damage arising from your use of the site.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms from time to time. We'll update the date at the top of the page. Continued use of the site after a change means you accept the updated terms.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@queenzone.org">privacy@queenzone.org</a>.</p>

  </div>
</section>
